<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Blank App Icons]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7922&amp;p=34176#p34176"><![CDATA[
That's weird that only some apps don't display their icons. From Run dialog (Win key+R), open:<br />shell:AppsFolder<br /><br />Locate these two app shortcuts there. Do the icons show in Explorer? If not, it's a Windows issue.<br /><br />Also, make sure you are using Classic Shell 4.3.1. From its Settings dialog -&gt; Backup button -&gt; click Clear cached information and see if the icons return.<br /><br />Also, the Windows icon cache may also have gotten corrupted. Try these two methods to fix that: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://winaero.com/blog/fix-broken-icons-and-reset-icon-cache-in-windows-10/">https://winaero.com/blog/fix-broken-ico ... indows-10/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Sep 21, 2017 4:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
